inn1.comm: short of a length, just outside off, sees it through to the keeper
lenght ball, just outside off, defended with an open face
looks to cut but the room is not available, and ends up under-edging it through to the keeper. Could easily have played this on
short of a length, closer to off, right behind it, defended to cover
full ball on off, driven to the left of mid-off to get off the mark
full on the pads, Sehwag clips it away to get off the mark himself
length ball on the pads, merely clipped away past midwicket, and it blazes across this outfield. Hyatt gives desperate chase, dives full length, but can't keep the ball in
short of a length, just outside off, punched away. Can't beat point
looks to punch this to leg, but is slightly early into the shot, and gets a soft leading edge towards mid-on. Along the ground
gets room outside off and punches this to third man for one
length ball, wide of off, GG doesn't go after it
this one nips back into Gambhir from just short of a length, hits him high on the thigh
short of a length, middle and off, Sehwag goes back and pushes this between square leg and midwicket
Gambhir looking to force the cut shot again. No room here either, and he can't time the shot
a nice effort ball. Digs this one in shorter, and gets extra bounce. Gambhir pulls out of the fend at last moment
length ball on the pads, clipped away fine of long leg where Hyatt does good work to keep them down to one
short of a length, just outside off, punched to cover

Upper-cut for a six. Sehwag is looking dangerous. This is dug in short, outside off, and Sehwag arches back to guide this over the slips. In the V behind the stumps it goes, and carries all the way. He has deliberately gone so fine
Gambhir walks down into this shot, and pushes a length ball to cover
tucked away off the hips for a single
short of a length, into the pads, tucked away for a single
length ball outside off, pushed to mid-off
length ball, swinging into the pads, Gambhir misses out, and is hit on the pad
length ball, middle and off, defended back to him
half-volley on the pads, smacked away for a four mercilessly through square leg
length ball on off, driven on the up, but can't beat mid-off
short of a length, there is room outside off, punched away to third man for one
Gambhir gets away now. This is short, angling away, provides him the width. Gambhir has to get tall to get on the top of the bounce, and places it between point and cover-point
steered away for four now. Deliberately opens the face to this length ball, and places it between the first and the wide slip
full on off, looks to drive, but can't beat cover
Sehwag pushes at a length ball from his crease and gets a thick outside edge towards third man, who is square

Sehwag survives a run-out chance! Gambhir played the short of a length ball towards point and Sehwag began running for the single. Gambhir took two steps down and stopped. Sehwag had run a long way down. Pollard fielded at point and Sehwag had given up. His only hope was if Pollard missed the direct hit at the bowler's end, which he did
defended on the off side, Gambhir begins to run, but Sehwag stays put
Gambjir steps out of his crease and carves a short of a length ball from outside off stump through point
defended on the off side
that's too far down leg side, Ramdin dives to his right to collect
Gambhir moves forward and across and taps the ball towards midwicket
a poor start, full and straight, Gambhir stays in his crease and flicks the ball off his pads through midwicket
Gambhir gets beaten after stepping out of his crease, making room by moving towards leg and trying to hit through the off
good length and straight, defended on the leg side

dropped! Gambhir pushed with hard hands at a length ball - it wasn't full enough to try and drive - the ball flew back at Russell, towards his left, and he couldn't catch it even though he got both hands to it
defended on the off side
too easy, a full toss outside off stump, Gambhir simply places it through cover and the ball flies off his bat
short of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
defended off the back foot, no room available
short of a length, into the pads, flicks it to short midwicket
short of a length, middle and off, defended back to him
nicely played, no room again, but he manoeuvres it with an open face, imparts power with the wrists. Between point and cover-point it goes
short, gets the width, but RR gets extra bounce too, which beats Sehwag's cut
short of a length, guided behind square for a single
Rampaul has just finished an over, and is slightly lazy to come down on this one. Sehwag has glanced this length ball to short fine leg, where Rampaul lets it through
driven on the up, powerfully too, but can't beat mid-on
length ball on off, no room, Sehwag defends off the front foot
wide down the leg side
short of a length, on the stumps, Sehwag plays with an open face, gets a single wide of cover
short, but no width. However, he glides it to third man with an open face
another steer to third man for a single
short of a length, a little bit of room available, and he guides it to third man
short, not too much room available, but Gambhir cuts it over Pollard at backward point. Pollard made it look close, but this was well over for any other man
short of a length, soft hands, open face, towards gully, and they steal a risky single. He would have made it even if Samuels had hit the stumps direct
length ball on off, there is no room available, Sehwag goes back towards leg, and opens the face late to get a single to third man
taps this short of a length delivery square on the off side
and Sehwag has been expecting Mr Narine. First ball. Length ball, outside off. Sehwag opens up a bit, and nonchalantly lofts it over long-on
plays this with an open face, past point for a single
good sharp and quick offbreak, starts around leg, bites away, beats the edge outside off
this starts too straight, and he works it away past square leg
this is the the one that goes the other away, but it is too short, and Sehwag cuts it away for one
another offspinner's wrong'un. Gambhir is surprised. He is shaping up to cut this, but it comes back in, and cramps him up
... and captain Sehwag dispatches him over long-off. Length ball outside off, and with nonchalance again, he goes inside-out, well over long-off
driven down to wide long-on for one
late-cuts this for a single
misses out on a length ball on the pads but takes a leg-bye
Gambhir walks down the track, but can't hit this one as there is no room available
gets the slightest bit of room here, and late-cuts it to the right of deep point
turning down the leg side, guided to fine leg for one
length ball outside off, driven down to long-off for one
defends this length ball outside off
covers the turn here, and pushes it past point for one
wants a quick single to short third man but is sent back
short of a length, on the pads, clipped away for a couple
slower ball, but well down the leg side, and turns further away. Ramdin has no chance
guides this shortish delivery to the right of third man, but gets only a single
rolls the fingers on this one, Gambhir opens the face, but can't beat backward point
angled into the pads this time, and is worked away for an easy single
good delivery to hush the crowd expecting Sehwag's fifty. This one seams away after pitching short of a length, and outside off. Beats Sehwag's open face
Sehwag stays on 49 for the time being, as this punch cannot beat point
length ball on off, turns away, pushed with an open face
offbreak again, on off, cuts it away, but can't beat the electric fence that Pollard is at point
the other one, but is starts too straight, and would have been a wide had Gambhir not deflected it deftly, past short fine leg. Hundred up for the stand
looks to work this to leg, from around off, gets a soft leading edge for a single into the covers
the away spinner again, Sehwag gets a leading edge towards cover

Air Virender is soaring high here. Goes to his fifty with a monstrous hit over long-on. This is pitched up enough to be in his swinging arc, and swing Sehwag does, well over long-on. His first fifty of the series
full, near yorker, outside off, and Gambhir squeezes it with an open face, past point, along the ground
and now Gambhir gets to fifty, dabbing this shortish ball square on the off side. Accepts the loud applause, and the receives a pat on the back from Sehwag
pushed back to Roach, who ricochets it towards mid-on, and Sehwag steals a single
full on off, squeezed out to third man for a single
yorker from Roach, full and straight, dug back to him
driven on the up, powerfully too, but long-on is back
low full toss on middle and leg, driven to long-on for one
driven nicely but not too far to the right of Sammy at cover. A fumble allows them the single
good yorker, Sehwag has made the room but can't do anything with the length

That's like hitting a spinner. This is bowled at 135ks, on a length, on middle and leg, in order to cramp him up. Sehwag charges at him, takes it on the half-volley, and makes room too to go over extra cover
short of a length and slower, and Sehwag rocks back and makes room to cut this to third man for one
another slower ball, this one beats Gambhir's attempt to run it down to third man
full toss on the pads, and dealt with accordingly. Deep square leg has no chance here. Sehwag now has more fours than he has sixes
half-volley on the pads, and the result is the same. Christmas has arrived 17 days too early for him
another full toss, but this time on off, and Sehwag can't beat cover-point
slower ball, short of a length, into the pads, worked away for a single to deep square

Run-out chance. GG wants a single after leaving the ball on the pitch. Sehwag is not interested. GG has to go back. A charging Roach has to go around Gambhir and is caught in a bit of a tangle. Can't field the ball, otherwise GG was struggling. Sammy appeals for obstruction of the field. A very polite, hope-against-hope query. Replays show that Gambhir did alter his course a little, by a foot maybe. Hard to tell, but the umpires not interested anyway
looks to run this behind square, but can't beat point
Sehwag looks to make room here, but this full ball swings further away and beats the edge
short of a length, on the stumps, defended back
queezes this full delivery out for a single
no quick single for GG this time. He takes a length ball and lofts it over mid-on. Easy does it
drops this at his fee, towards cover, and takes a quick single
full, away-swinging delivery. Nearly a yorker, but it provides him width, and Sehwag squeezes it to the left of point and well to the right of third man
full toss, just outside off, gets only the single to third man

another run-out opportunity. Full, on the pads, clipped to the left of deep square. Seems like the two is no, but Gambhir turns it down. Sehwag has to put in a dive to get back in. I am not sure I have ever seen Sehwag dive into the crease
this is why GG wanted to stay on the strike perhaps. Gets a length ball into the pads, and deflects it wide of fine leg for four
looks to push this with an open face, can't beat the ring
steered away to third man for a single
short and wide, looks to run this down to third man, is beaten by the extra bounce
length ball around off, steers this down to third man, brings up the 150 of the stand
This is high ball and long ball at the same time. Length ball, middle and leg, and he has hit it high enough to bring down rain, but it has also cleared long-on with ease
short of a length, extra bounce, hits him in the rib area, goes for a leg-bye
short of a length, into the pads, worked away for a single
into the hips again, but this time Sehwag gets bat on it, glancing it wide of the keeper and fine of fine leg
this shortish delivery stays low, but Sehwag has punched it down to long-on without trouble
and Samuels isn't spared either. Sehwag knows Samuels fires them in, so waits back for the first ball, gets some room, and uses the pace to guide this between point and short third
another quick ball, nearly a yorker, dug out
another quick near-yorker, driven to long-off for one
a slower offbreak this time, pushed with an open face for a single
quick again, hit back to Samuels
low full toss, driven down to long-on for a single
short of a length, on off, pushed with an open face, gets a single
looks to guide this down to third man, but the offcutter bounces a little more than he expects, and beats him
tucked away off the hip for a single, Sehwag back on strike

short, wide, smoked away over point. The fielder has got a finger to it, and I am surprised the finger is in tact. Sehwag's bat is in his left hand, raised high above his head. The crowd on its feet. The gallery too. Sehwag takes his time to soak in the applause

Gambhir is gone. Good work by Samuels at straight extra cover. Sehwag punches this down the track, thinks he can get an easy single to long-ff, to which GG responds too. But Samuels act fast and intercepts. Sehwag now sends Gambhir back. The bowler hasn't yet come back to the stumps, so Samuels needs a direct hit. He produces one
tries the pull, but the ball is not short enough, and he finds midwicket. On the bounce
Raina off the mark with a drive down to long-on
full, fast and straight, gets a single to long-on
looks to drive this to the extra cover region. There is no turn on the ball, and he ends up getting an inside edge back to the bowler
goes straighter down the ground this time, and gets a single to long-off
short of a length, quick and accurate, pushed back to Samuels
full on the pads, takes another single to long-on
slower ball, full on the pads, driven to long-on for one
short of a elngth, on the stumps, Raina moves across to pull it fine for a single
slower ball, short, pulled away not sweetly, gets just the single to deep square
punches this on the up, down to long-off for one
bowled from wide of the crease, angling in, short of a length, hit powerfully, but Sehwag can't beat point
slower ball, on the stumps, punched away between long-on and deep midwicket. Comes back for two
angling into the pads, pushed with soft hands into the leg side
low full toss on the pads, but Sehwag can't beat midwicket
long hop, on the pads, and the square leg umpire is sent ducking. Those are free runs, and Sehwag doesn't say no
full on off, driven powerfully to long-off for one
flighted on off, Raina plays with an open face, gets a single to sweeper-cover
full toss, Sehwag gets just the single to long-on, moves off the Nelson
quick hands from Sehwag. Short of a length, no room, and he late-cuts it to third man. It flies towards the man there, who has been placed fine just for that
Raina is thinking of the pull as this short of a length, but it is also outside off, and Raina checks the shot in the end
gift upon gift upon gift. Short, well down the leg side, and Raina helps it along his way with a pull for four
this boundary has been earned. Short of a length, outside off, and he plays the square cut slightly late to find the gap between point and cover-point. Third man stands no chance
and he follows it up with an earned pair. Bunts this off the pads, between the two deep men on the leg side, and hares back for two
short of a length, accurate, Raina defends it back
full on off, smashed down to long-off for a single. Samuels could have dived for this one, but that wouldn't have been a healthy choice
full outside off, driven to sweeper-cover
fired full and fast into the pads, helped away for a single
slower through the air, accurate, pushed to extra cover
this one is pushed to the right of extra cover, and despite Sammy's dive he gets a single
drives this with an open face, gets a single to sweeper-cover
Narine's other one. Sehwag tries to sweep but is beaten. However this can't be given lbw because it hasn't straightened enough
drives this one to sweeper-cover for a single
short of a length, on the stumps, pushed down to long-off for one
another offspinner's wrong'un, but it starts around leg and doesn't straighten enough to get him the leg-before
this is the regulation offbreak, and turns well down the leg side
short of a length, on the pads, pushed to straight midwicket

top-quality shot. Short of a length, quick, no room, and Sehwag stands there nonchalantly to guide it fine on the leg side. This is not a sweep, not a pull. Not even a scoop. More like a vertical sweep
length ball outside off, driven straight to straight extra cover
strong off side in place, and he takes this from outside off and bunts it into the on side for a single
quick, into the pads, flicked away for a single
short of a length, cut away to the left of cover-point, gets a single

He has sold Samuels the dummy. This is straight out of poker. Makes room early, Samuels follows him, and Sehwag shuffles across to get inside the line and scoop this away for a four. Saleem Malik would have approved
short of a length, turning in, worked away into the leg side
charges at him, is beaten in the flight, and mis-hits it, which is just as well because the mis-hit means it doesn't carry to long-on
runs this offbreak behind square for a single
wide down the leg side. Starts outside leg, and keeps going
well bowled. This one goes the other way, after it is flighted around off. Beats the edge
quicker one, on the pads, worked away for a single
worked away off the pads for a single to fine leg
the away-spinner again, but Sehwag seems to be reading them now, and pushes this to sweeper-cover for one
full toss, driven inside-out, but gets just the single to long-off
flighted on middle and off, driven back to Samuels
shortish, wide, and quick. Raina goes for the cut, gets a bit of a top edge, but he has found the gap between point and short third man
pushes this to the left of point with soft hands, gets a single
full, near yorker, pushed back to Samuels
appeal for lbw, a mild one, as Sehwag is beaten on the reverse sweep. This is a length ball, pitched outside off, and quick. The umpire must think Sehwag has got outside the line
lovely shot. Sehwag is definitely picking those awayspinners, and he makes room to take this length ball from just outside off, and punches it to left of sweeper-cover
one better than the other. Narine goes for the old-fashioned flight this time, and Sehwag's response is to come down the track, right down to the pitch of it, and wallop it over Narine' head
looks to work this around the corner, but finds short fine leg
fullish, around middle and leg, driven to long-off for one
flighted outside off, pushed down past the diving straight extra cover
turning down the leg side, Ramdin appeals for the catch. Tony Hill seems to have been bluffed. Doesn't call it a wide. Sehwag lets Ramdin know exactly what he thinks, and they have a good laugh
short of a length outside off, opens the face, over to Sehwag
he is looking to make room, but Samuels follows him, and all Sehwag manages is a hit back to the bowler
Carved away for four. This is taken from off, and he has not even tried to hit this powerfully. The inside edge is visible to the batsman as he opens the face, and places it past point
short of a length, on off, eased away for a single to long-on
no turn here, and he gets Raina's bottom edge as he looks to run it down. It doesn't find the stumps, though
short of a length, outside off, punched away to deep cover this time
Rains slogs at him right away, and finds the gap between long-on and deep square even though this is a mis-hit
wide of the crease, angling in, pushed to midwicket
mid-on is up in the circle, and Raina has exploited it. Russell is angling this in from some angle, allowing Raina to swing freely. He goes with the angle, and clears mid-on easily
pace and bounce here, as Raina looks to late-cut this and is beaten
short of a length, slower ball, on off, pushed to cover for one
short of a length, on the stumps, Sehwag makes room, pushes this to the right of point for one
long hop, but Sehwag doesn't make the most of it, gets just the single to deep midwicket
low full toss, Raina gets a single to cover

full toss this time, Sehwag doesn't get four, but he has hit it left enough of Pollard at deep midwicket to come back for two. That takes him to 151, and he looks fresh. No sings of tiredness. Accepts another generous applause
Sehwag keeps going. Low full toss, and he carves it to the right of extra cover. No power. Just the opening of the face and timing
another beauty from Sehwag. A length ball on off, but he has opened the face again, and placed this between backward point and cover-point
Raina is ducking for his life here. Drilled down the ground, and he has to act swiftly to prevent damage. Sehwag gets a single to long-on
driven on the up, can't beat extra cover
low full toss from wide of the crease, driven to long-on for one
length ball outside off, driven inside-out, but the extra cover is on the fence
slight low bounce on this short delivery angling in. Hits him on the pad, but is headed down leg

this one bounces well and truly, and Sehwag well and truly pulls it for six. Over midwicket he goes into the tobacco-sponsored boundary boards. It might be the chewing tobacco, but Sehwag is smoking them here. Who cares about the health department regulations?
gets just the single this time, to deep square leg, but retains strike. Not short enough to be pulling
length ball on middle and leg, driven to long-on. Pollard fumbles, Sehwag wants two, but he has taken only a couple of steps by the time Pollard rockets the throw back. Back in the nick of time
slower ball, full on off, driven to long-off for one
wide down the leg side
another wide down the leg side, they dare not bowl at him
looks to hits this length ball into the on side, gets an inside edge on to the pad, and takes a single to point
low full toss outside off, driven down to long-off

Sammy, oh Sammy. They cannot believe it. Sitter dropped. Sehwag looks to go inside-out, ends up slicing it, Sammy runs back and to his left from extra cover. Gets under it. In she goes and pops out. Ravi Rampaul's jaw has dropped. How can he drop this? This seems to have settled in for a second, but doesn't stay. Sehwag points at Sammy with his bat. Must be thanking him
driven down to long-off for a single
length ball on the pads, bunts this to midwicket, dives full length for a single
full toss on the pads, but finds midwicket
another full toss, another flick, another stop at midwicket. Two dots in a row

well bowled, fires in a yorker down the leg side, Sehwag's bat goes up high, but doesn't come down ever. The ball hits the heel and goes to the fine leg fence. Tony Hill is alert and doesn't allow leg-byes. No shot is offered here
driven down to long-on for one
this one had a shot offered all right. Yorker outside off, Raina goes low, and opens the face, squeezing it past the keeper. Third man has no way to get around. This outfield is too quick
nearly bowled him. A lovely yorker on the stumps, Sehwag just about keeps it out. Leaves the ball in his crease and scrambles a single. Three hundred up inside 40 overs
tucked away off the hips, and over to Sehwag
length ball no the pads, flicked away wristily past square leg, casually moves to his personal best and the highest by any player against West Indies
pushed wide of long-on, wants the second, but is sent back. Rightly so, as the throw is accurate
and quietly on the side Raina has got himself a fifty, off 42 balls. Drives this length ball to long-off for one
and the gifts continue to arrive. Half-volley on the pads, with fine leg up inside the circle. He moves slightly inside the line, and clips it away for four
poor fielding. Hit powerfully but straight to backward point where Simmons doesn't get his body behind it, and allows it to squeeze through his legs

full toss on middle and leg, pushed down to long-off. He has played it with soft hands, takes Russell on, but the throw is directed at Raina's end and is deadly accurate. Raina is caught short despite the dive. Two wickets gone both run-outs. It was actually Sehwag's call to come back for the second after they had ambled for the first run
starts with a thick edge to third man for a single

lovely batting. He has run two men out today, but if he keeps doing this there is no risk. A low full toss, just outside off, and he has opened the face and somehow found the timing to send it for four past point
driven to long-on now, reaches 187, Australia's number of devil
opens the face on this length ball, gets a single, keeps the strike
short of a length outside off, punched to the left of deep point, comes back for two
full outside off, driven to the right of point, they take a single despite Samuels's diving save
slower ball on the stumps, punched down the ground, Sammy gets a hand to it to his left, but they manage a single off the defelction
another slower ball, Jadeja waits for it before hitting it to the left of point. Comes back for the second. Another trhow at Sehwag's end. He has to run hard again
short of a length, into the body, punched down to long-on for one
slower ball again, opens the face, takes the single to short third man. And they take the overthrow because Sammy has omitted to collect the throw
short of a length, into the body, worked away for a single
slower ball, short, on the pads, pulled away to deep midwicket for one
length ball on off, pushed to extra cover, and they go at Sehwag's end again, and he has to run hard to make it
... but there are other gifts available. A juicy full toss outside leg, and he helps it along over short fine. 8000 runs for Sehwag. One hit short of a double century
short of a length, on the pads, worked away for a single. Now only one man stand ahead of him. SRT
Jadeja gives Pollard the charge, and is cramped up by this short ball into his body. Hit high on the thigh pad
crowd goes wild as Sehwag late-cuts this, but he can't beat the diving man at point, and gets just a single
and finally a catch has been taken. Jadeja plays an ungainly flick-pull to a slower short ball that has cramped it up. The ball is dying on the midwicket, but Rampaul runs in and takes it low

There it is. Sehwag is the second man to reach a double-century in ODIs. A man has run onto the field with flowers for Viru. He cuts this past point, to the right of third man. No chance for the diving man. He punches the air in delight. Pure delight. Hugs Rohit Sharma. Then takes his time to acknowledge all sections of the crowd. Removes the helmet. Casts a glance at the sky. Pure delight. Tendulkar is somewhere in a Singapore Airlines flight. Or he might have just reached Australia. His record is no more
low full toss, hits it to long-off for one
length ball on off, pushed wide of extra cover for a single
Whoa. Sehwag hits another gear. Upper-cuts this for a six. Square, and not fine. So he has imparted some power on it too. That's 134 runs in boundaries. 22 behind Watson's record of 150
dabs this behind square, to the right of third man, comes back for two
full and straight, hit to long-on, brings Sehwag back on strike
short, on the pads, pulled away to deep square for a single
short of a length, on off, dabbed away for a single
plays the pick-up shot off the pads, but doesn't quite time it. Gets it right enough of deep square to survive, though
Sharma gives him the charge, Pollard follows him down leg, the fine leg is up, and has to dive to keep them down to one. Has injured his knee in the process
full outside off, driven to long-off for one
Sehwag is looking to make room, RR follows him, and the cramped batsman can only get a single to long-on
Sharma joins the party here. Length ball outside off, and he has smashed this past extra cover. Along the ground
slower ball, on the stumps, pushed towards long-on for a single
mid-off has come up so that they can bowl straight at him, but Sehwag makes room successfully this time, and he lofts a full ball over mid-off
Sehwag back away, RR slips in a bouncer, over the stumps. Sehwag doesn't play any shot
Pollard continues bowling the slower ones, is hit to long-on for a single

Sehwag really doesn't need these gifts I tell you, but if you keep serving them up, he will keep smacking them. Short, outside leg, nothing behind the delivery, and guides it to the right of short fine leg. Hundred runs in fours alone

He is gone. He hasn't batted 50 overs till, but look at that score. Sehwag has mis-hit this attempt at hitting a six over long-off. Ends up skying this to Martin at long-off. Almost every West Indian has come up to shake his hand before he walks off. Rohit congratulates him too. And just before he crosses the fence, Sehwag looks back and raises his bat for the crowd. Lovely response from them
flicked wide of long-on, and they come back for the second
hit wide of long-on again, but it will be just the single
full, on the pads, off the mark with a flick
full on off, driven to deep point for a single
full outside off again, hit to extra cover for a single
West Indies can do without juicy full tosses. Sharma easily lofts it over mid-off for another boundary. Four hundred is the next landmark
Sharma goes inside-out again, but ends up slicing this wide of point. Wide enough to send it for another four
full and straight, looking to cramp him up, Sharma makes room and drives it past cover, comes back for two
that's more of what you need on such days. A yorker at 145ks. Bounces about 10 inches short of the stumps, and takes the off pole out. Sharma is beaten by the pace of it
Kohli gives him the charge, hits this slower ball to deep midwicket
slower ball, driven on the up, gets a single to deep cover
one slower ball too many. Kohli is waiting for it this time, and lofts it wide of long-on. The massacre continues

short and wide, too wide, and India's 400 comes up. Kohli, though, has overbalanced trying to cut this, and Ramdin - standing up - has attempted a stumping. The replays show he is fine. India's fourth 400. The next bext is two times
Kohli gives him the charge and is beaten by a slower ball well outside off
this is the quicker delivery, holds its line outside off, and beats his drive
Kohli is certain this will be the slower delivery. Waits and waits for it to arrive before going inside-out over extra cover
gives him the charge, Pollard bowls short and into the body, Kohli manages to hit it wide enough fo long-on to be able to come back for two
full outside off, driven to long-off for one
full toss on the pads, driven wide of deep midwicket, and they come back for a second
full toss on the stumps, driven down to long-on for a single. Misses out on this one
yorker on middle and leg, squeezes it out for a single
full on the pads, flicked away between long-on and deep midwicket, comes back for two

fittingly West Indies end the innings with a full toss to sum up their effort. Kohli sums India's effort up by driving it wide of extra cover for a four. That brings up India's highest score in ODIs too

inn2.comm: Simmons can shuffle across without worrying about any movement, and pushes this to square leg
short of a length, around off, pushed to cover
short of a length, outside off, steered past second slip
length ball on the pads, driven down to mid-on
pushes this to mid-on, starts off for a single, and then sends Powell back. Just in the nick of time
nicely played. Short of a length, straight, Simmons moves inside the line, and clips it between midwicket and mid-on. All along the ground
Powell improvises. Premeditates the sweep, ends up playing almost a Dilscoop over the keeper for four
fired into the pads and dabbed down on the leg side
short but didn't bounce much. Pull is bottom edged to square leg
flighted on a length. Simmons leans forward and pushes to the off side
fired into the pads again. Powell flicks uppishly and square leg is interested but it goes past him

and Rahul Sharma makes his first contribution. But Powell has run himself out here. Simmons just pushed the ball to the off side and Powell bolted down the pitch as if a firecracker had been set off near him. Was halfway down the pitch and Rahul Sharma just had to toss the ball back to Ashwin who removed the bails
short of a length on off stump and steered down to third man
short of a length and Simmons punches to point
short of a length on off stump and punched to mid-on for one
that's edged between the keeper and first slip. Would not have been a catch because Samuels had loosened his wrists and kept it down. But still frustrating for Vinay
good length again from Vinay and Samuels punches to mid-off
another good ball is defended
Simmons breaks free. Steps out, gets to the pitch and smashes it over long-on. Classic shot off an offspinner, clean timing and great elevation. Goes several rows back
Ashwin slows the pace and Simmons has to wait for the ball to arrive
again Ashwin takes a pause before delivering, possibly waiting to see if Simmons is going to charge him. He bowls it short of a length and it's nudged to the leg side
short and cut hard past point. That was a gimme ball from Vinay, and Simmons helped himself
that's a delightful back-foot drive. He's timing the ball superbly. Short of a length outside off stump, a bit of room and Simmons rocks back and punches it between point and cover
and that's the best of the lot. He's paddle-sweeped, yes paddle-sweeped Vinay. Premeditated, Vinay pitched full on off, Simmons made perfect contact and gets it past fine-leg
better line and length and Simmons defends
short of a length, defended off the back foot back to the bowler
good comeback from Vinay, Another short-of-a-length ball on off stump is defended back to him. Three dots after being hit for three fours.
flat on off stump and defended back
nice tight line from Ashwin and another dot ball
Samuels tries to punch this through the covers but can't pick the gap
slightly shorter and punched to mid-off
slow through the air and Simmons wound up but ended up just pushing to mid-on
appeal but that's off the pad to leg slip. Sliding down the leg side, Samuels tried to flick and it goes off his right pad
short of a length and punched to over
that's hammered back. Simmons gave himself room, Vinay didn't change his line and Simmons had room to take a golf swing and get it past mid-on. Not timed perfectly, but enough power to get four
Vinay tucks him up with a short ball on off stump and Simmons steers to third man
Samuels makes room and plays a lazy looking drive. Doesn't time it. Rahul Sharma dives to his left to field it neatly
nicely bowled, coming into Simmons and he gets a thick inside-edge onto his pads
again Samuels makes room but this time he gets the timing right. He slaps a short-of-a-length ball between cover and point for four. The fifty is up for West Indies already!
and immediately causes Simmons problems. Flat and angled in and Simmons plays and misses
a bit short but Simmons can't time the cut
tries the cut again but there's too much pace from Jadeja
a little fuller and Simmons just pushes it to cover
similar ball and another dot
wow, Jadeja's bowled a maiden on this pitch. This one is on of stump and Simmons defends
length ball, played to cover
a bit short and Samuels looks for a big pull but bottom-edges
has a swing at a ball on off stump but it's straight to the lively Rohit Sharma at cover point
nicely bowled, tucked him up with one angled in and Samuels can only punch to mid-off
that's slapped through extra-cover. Nothing much wrong with the ball but Samuels had made up his mind to drive hard. It was in his slot and he got the timing right

this one goes to cover's left. Slightly shorter and Samuels was again winding up before the bowler reached the crease. He swings and times it well. Can't really call that a drive. More an off forehand
that's nicely worked by Simmons. Went back in the crease, waited for it and rolled his wrists over the pull to get it to deep midwicket for four
slower this time on off stump and Simmons opens the face to push to point
the attempted cut is edged to the keeper. That wasn't short enough, Simmons ricked back, went really hard at it but only managed a thick edge. The ball bobbled in Parthiv's gloves but he held on
defends his first ball
and goes hard at his second. Was quit wide from Jadeja and Hyatt can't time an attempted off drive. Goes in the air but mid-off is back on the boundary
closer to off and pushed to cover
short of a length on off and punched to cover
that's quite wide and goes off the outside edge to third man. Could have possibly got more from that ball
that's been clubbed over midwicket. Samuels again had a big backlift. Mithun seemed to roll his fingers over the ball but it was right in Samuels' slot and he's baseball-swung it over midwicket
that's wide. Mithun's been thrown off by the last shot and sprays it too wide of off
another six! Samuels is not going to die wondering. This one is picked up from a length and deposited over long-on.
wide of off and played to deep cover
short of a length and punched to the off side
super stop from Kohli a backward point. Was short from Rahul, and Samuels cut hard but Kohli flew to his left to prevent the boundary
fuller and it's defended back
short again and Samuels eyes lit up. But he's cut it straight to Kohli at backward point
first hint of turn. Pitched on middle and turned to off. Samuels punches to the off side and they run a quick single
pitched on leg and it's driven to long-on

and Rahul Sharma has his first international wicket. Its a topspinner and Samuels tried to cut. There was no sidespin and he's bottom edged it onto his stumps. Rahul's victory run has ended somewhere around the point boundary. He's clearly quite excited
short of a length and punched back. The non-striker was hurrying back but Mithun couldn't flick it onto the stumps
pushed to the off side
good ball on off stump and Hyatt mis-times the attempted drive
short of a length and punched hard uppishly past cover. Raina was flying to his left but it's a foot away from him.
that's hammered down the ground. Mithun pitches on a length again again, rolled his fingers over it, and Hyatt just hit through the line over mid-on
slightly slower from Mithun and Hyatt pushes to cover
quick through the air from Rahul and Ramdin gets on the back foot and punches to long-on
on off stump and Hyatt plays it late to backward point
slower this time and Hyatt gets on the front foot and defends
appeal for an lbw but that was sliding down leg. Pitched on leg and didn't straighten enough
another appeal for leg before and this looks closer. It was the googly, pitched on off, hit in front of middle and probably would have hit the top of leg stump

bowled him. So this is why this bloke's in the team. A quick legspinner has done Hyatt through the legs. Hyatt was coming down the track, but he's got in a real tangle. The ball pitches outside leg stump, Hyatt stretches to reach the pitch but it turns straight through his legs. What a start to Rahul Sharma's career. Two wickets in two overs. Another five-for for a debutant?
short of a length and punched back.
coming from just outside off and Ramdin just pushes to mid-on
that's angled into the pads and nudged for a single to deep square leg
just outside off and Pollard is off the mark with a push to cover
Mithun strays down leg but that's really well placed by Ramdin. Got it to the right of deep square leg for a boundary
that's driven to the left of mid-off but a neat stop from Jadeja prevents four
fired in full at leg stump and Pollard has to dig it out
another big appeal for lbw but that's hit just outside off. Everything else was right about it. Was the googly and would have taken off, but well done by the umpire to spot the point of impact
that's pushed to long-on
that was the googly again and Pollard plays off the back foot
fuller and Ramdin drives to long-on

short and Pollard's missed it! That was really short but it was the topspinner. Pollard had a big swing but he's completely missed the ball and it's hit the top of off. Rahul Sharma must think he's in a dream
angled across and nudged to the leg side
angled in to the right-hander and nudged for one
slow through the air and angled into his pads. Russell plays it watchfully to midwicket
this one straightens from middle to off and Russell defends off the back foot
pitched on off and pushed to long-off
that's pitched on middle and defended back
quick one on off and pushed to mid-off
and there's a reality check. Fuller and Russell gets down quickly and slog-sweeps him way over midwicket. Real power and timing in that shot
great comeback. Quick topspinner kept low and Russell was in trouble defending off the back foot
flat again but Rusell defends more easily this time
flat and angled in, worked away to square leg
slightly slower through the air but Ramdin waits for it nicely and nudges to the on side
Jadeja continues and angles one in. Defended back
Ramdin pushes to backward point
full and driven in the direction of long-off, but Raina rushes across from cover to cut off the single
flighted and pushed back to the bowler
driven hard but finds the fielder at cover point
on off stump and defended back
that's turned from middle to off and defended back
and more turn. Pitches on leg this time and Rusell nees to adjust quickly as it turns quite sharply
what a responses. Fuller ball and he's just teed off. A clean strike over long-off
goes for the sweep and that's dangerous against Rahul's pace. But he manages to just about control it
slower through the air and Russell gets forward to defend
defended off the back foot but it was quite full and Russell had to adjust late to prevent it from sneaking through
pushed to cover
driven to long-on
shorter and cut to deep point. Vinay Kumar does well to get across and keep it to two
pushed to the off side
slow through the air and Ramdin works it to midwicket.
in the blockhole and Russell digs it out
slow through the air and Ramdin gets well forward to defend
fuller and flicked to the leg side

that's gone out of the ground! slower through the air, Russell got down to slog-sweep. He wasn't quite to the pitch but that only helped him get more elevation. It's gone sailing over the scoreboard at midwicket and the ball's lost
pushed down leg side and nudged to deep square leg
Rahul's not been scared out of maintaining a slower pace. Pitched on off and defended
googly and Ramdin nudges it to long-on
pushed off the back foot to long-off
defended off the front foot back to the bowler
stifled appeal for an lbw but probably a bit high. That was the straighter one and hit in front off middle but high on the front pad
steps forward and takes it on the full. Driven wide of long-off for four
played off the back foot this time to square leg
played to deep backward square leg
flat ball is driven to long-on

appeal for a stumping ans that's gone. Russell was attempting a sweep and he's dragged his back foot out of the crease. The ball from Raina was angled across the right-hander and it beat the bat. Parthiv was quick to remove the bails
short of a length and punched to the off side
Sammy defends off the back foot
big backlift and the big swing hits the inside-half of the bat and goes to deep square leg
slower through the air, Ramdin waits for it and works it to the leg side
slow through the air and defended off the front foot
Sammy hung on the back foot this time and had to adjust late. Pushes it behind square on the off side
turning from off to middle and worked to fine leg

that's short and slapped straight down Mithun's throat at long-off. That's disappointing from Sammy. It was a long hop and Sammy could have hit anywhere. He's chosen to flat bat it in the air to long-off.
slow through the air and defended off the back foot
nice line and defended
googly takes the outside half of the bat to backward point
flat through the air and defended
flat again and defended
this one pitches on leg and it's worked away easily for a single
turns from middle to off but Ramdin plays against the turn and works it to the leg side
turns into the left-hander and he works it with the turn to midwicket
slow through the air and defended
defended off the front foot again
shorter and Rampaul attempts a cut but it's straight to backward point
that was really short but Rampaul again can't find the gap with the cut
pushed to the off side
short and turns from outside leg to middle stump, Rampaul works it against the turn to the leg side
wide of off stump and Rampaul drives hard  but it goes off the toe of the bat to deep cover
full on off stump and driven to long-on
poor ball away outside leg and swept away to fine leg for four
a stifled appeal for lbw. Turning from middle and would probably have gone down leg
defended off the front foot
full and Rampaul digs it out of the blockhole
full and pushed back to the bowler
in the blockhole and squeezed out to midwicket
slower through the air and beat Ramdin. Hits him on the pad but would have turned down leg
turning from middle to leg, pushed to midwicket
short and Ramdin pulls in the air to deep square leg for four. Ashwin dragged that down and deserved to be punished. Ramdin obliges
flicked with the turn to the leg side
fired in at leg stump and played to deep square leg
pushed to mid-off
shorter and punched to cover
short and punched back to the bowler
misses the attempted cut. Close to the edge that one. A sigh from Raina
flighted from Jadeja and the attmempted cover drive is mis-timed
misses the sweep and it goes off the pad to deep square leg
defended off the front foot
full and driven to long-off
slower and defended off the back foot
that's pushed to deep cover point for one
pushed to backward point
a bit of turn and it squares up Rampaul. Goes off the outside edge to backward point along the ground
misses the cut again. That was short enough but Rampaul was late on the shot
angled in towards and leg and defended back
short of a length and punched off the back foot to long-on. Raina went scampering across trying to save the single but it beats him
short and Ramdin pulls backward of square. Well fielded by Ajinkya Rahane on the boundary to stop the four
full on leg stump and patted back

straight down long-on's throat. The attempted slog-sweep is well-timed but the placement is all wrong. That went really flat too. Not enough elevation. Went quickly to long-on who took the catch at waist height
fired in and takes the inside edge onto to pad
beats the bat. Nicely flighted and turns from off away from the batsman. Roach fishes and misses it
outside off again and pushed to deep cover
angled in on middle stump and defended back
slow through the air and Ramdin gets well forward to defend
pitched up and driven to long-on
straighter one takes the inside edge. Roach was well beaten there. Luckily for him the edge doesn't go to hand
turned from middle to off and defended back
short and pulled to deep square leg
very full and defended straight back
full and defended back
full and swept to deep square leg
angled in and just nudged to the leg side
that turned but kept down nicely. Goes along the ground to second slip
a stumping appeal but India don't seem to confident. And he's well in. Foot never left the crease. Was well beaten by Jadeja though. Good use of flight
angled in and defended
pitched outside leg and worked away to deep square leg
beats the outside edge with the legspinner. Perfect ball. Pitched on off, turned away and Ramdin is not even close to it
pushed down to long-on
quicker one and Roach is hurried on the back foot
that was the googly. Slow through the air but Roach reads it well and defends off the front foot
short and punched to cover
angled in and flicked to short fine leg
That was not that short but Ramdin rocks back and cuts it through the covers. Really good shot that. first boundary in a while
slower through the air and pushed to long-on
on off stump and defended back
that was wide and gave Roach room to swing his arms. He takes the opportunity and clubs one past the bowler
this one is closer to off and defended
nicely timed. Hit against the turn to the long-off fence. Just one confident step out and smashes the lofted off drive
played to deep cover
that's defended off the back foot
driven off the front foot and finds the fence at cover. First fifty for Ramdin since 2007. Reaches with it a classic cover drive
quicker and defended back
it's down the leg side and turning further down. Ramdin misses the sweep but it's a wide
that's another good drive to the cover boundary from Ramdin. He's looking really good now
pushed to long-on
defended off the back foot
tries an expansive drive and it's brilliantly stopped by Raina at short cover. But he's hurt himself doing it. Stays on the field though

driven straight back to the bowler. Roach clearly lost his patience. Tried to hit Jadeja down the ground but didn't get to the pitch and the ball just stopped in him. Went back quite quickly but Jadeja holds on for his 50th ODI wicket
defends his first ball
on a good length and defended back
that's short and Ramdin has found the cover fence again. This time with a hard cut
driven to long-on
angled in from around the wicket and straightening. Narine defends
but he's driven that quite confidently to long-on
that's just slapped away to midwicket. He was looking to slog-sweep but made contact while still one the way down. Absolutely hammered to the boundary
first ball is on a length and defended
short and cut to the deep cover point fielder
short again from Rohit and Ramdin looks for the big pull. Doesn't bounce that much but he gets it away to deep square leg
Narine gets down and rolls his wrists over the sweep. Places it well too, backward of square leg for four
pushes to long-off
punched to long-on
angled in and straightening. Narine defends
a bit of room and he goes for the big drive but it goes under the bat to the keeper
slower through the air and defended
slow again and Narine works it away to square leg
Ramdin goes deep in the crease and times it well to get another four on the off side. Not that short but he got back quickly to cut
gets on the front foot this time and punches back
played to midwicket
uses the wrists nicely to work it to the leg side
Narine takes a couple of steps down the pitch and drives to long-off
a thick outside-edge runs away to the third-man boundary. Jadeja makes a good attempt on the boundary but can't pull it in
worked to the leg side
short of a length and punched off the back foot to long-off
driven to long-off
pushed to cover
driven to cover again
this time he drives it slightly squarer and gets one to the sweeper
Ramdin gets forward and pushes to back to the bowler
rocks back this time and punches to the extra-cover fielder
appeal but there's a faint inside edge onto the pad. Angled in from Rohit and beat Narine in the flight
steps out and smashed over long-on. That came out of the blue. But a really confident, well-timed on-drive
rocks back and punches to short cover
goes on the back foot again and punches down the ground
that's wide down the leg side and Ramdin connects with the sweep. Finds the fielder at deep square though, so just the single
nice line and Narine defends
well-timed drive from Ramdin. He made room, cleared the front foot and just laced it past cover
worked to the leg side
Narine punches back
worked to the leg side
short of a length and Ramdin went hard at it. Smashed off the back foot but stopped well at short extra cover
worked to the leg side
short of a length and nudged to midwicket
more confidence from Narine. Steps down the track, didn't get to the pitch but smashes it on the up past extra cover
pitched on leg and worked away to square leg
worked away to the leg side
short of a length and the cut is bottom-edged
full and defended easily
rocks back but can't time the punch and finds short extra cover
back- foot drive finds midwicket
full and driven hard but long-on gets across quickly to his left to keep it to one
full and defended  back to the bowler
full on off stump and driven to cover point
angled in and defended back
that's a big full toss and Ramdin just slams it to midwicket. Shocking ball from Rohit
this one pitches and driven to long-on
pushed to cover point
short and punched off the back foot to the vacant cover fence
full on middle stump and defended off the front foot
nice length and Narine defends
that's played to long-on. But Ramdin refuses the single. He wants the ton
and he's thrown it away. Skies an attempted slog-sweep and mid-on keeps his nerve to hold a really high catch
